Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Remove the packaging from the @Linda McCartney Sausages{6}(apart from the metal tray). Drizzle with a little @oil{} and then bake them (in their tray) on the middle shelf of your oven until crispy on the outside, about ~{15-16%minutes}.

Meanwhile, chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Add the potatoes to the boiling water and simmer until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

While the potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{150} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Stir fry until the mushrooms are browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Pour in the @water{150}. Add the @red wine stock paste{28} and @redcurrant jelly{25}, stir to dissolve. Bring to the boil and simmer until really nicely reduced, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{125} in handfuls and stir through to wilt, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the veggie sausages to the sauce and stir to coat. Remove from the heat.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain them in a #colander{} and pop back in the saucepan. Add some @?plant based milk{} and @?butter{} (if you have it, or you can use dairy if you prefer). Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Add a splash of water to the sauce if it's a bit thick. Spoon the mash into wide #bowls{} and serve the sausage stew and sauce alongside. Enjoy!